:~$ cat /etc/hosts (hostname and IP address configuration file)
:~$ ping <hostname> (To test connection between systems)
:~$ ifconfig (To view configuration of network interface)
:~$ ethtool <nic name> (query or control network driver and hardware settings)
:~$ host google.com (DNS lookup utility)
:~$ nslookup google.com (lookup name server interactively)
:~$ dig google.com  (lookup domain name infromation from nameserver)
:~$ route (give routing information)
:~$ traceroute <hostname> (print the route packets trace to network host)
:~$ nmap -A -T4 google.com (Port scanner)
:~$ namap -sP <IP/CIDR> (No of hosts connected to the system)
:~$ tcpdump -i <nic name> (dump traffic on a network)
:~$ iptraf (Interactive Colorful IP LAN Monitor)
